quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
  100,10,"and the secrets of the hearts will be brought to light<sup>7</sup>?","[7] i.e., when all secrets of the hearts and faiths are made known."
  100,11,"Indeed, their Lord is All-Aware of them on that Day<sup>8</sup>.","[8] Nothing of their affairs will be hidden from Him."
  101,1,"The Striking Calamity!",""
  101,2,"What is the Striking Calamity?",""
  101,3,"How do you know what the Striking Calamity is?",""
  101,4,"On that Day people will be like scattered moths<sup>1</sup>,","[1] After having been thrown out of their graves."
  101,5,"and the mountains will be like carded wool<sup>2</sup>.","[2] As they disintegrate."
  101,6,"Then the one whose scales of good deeds are heavy,",""
  101,7,"will have a pleasant life<sup>3</sup>.","[3] In Paradise."
  101,8,"But the one whose scales of good deeds are light,",""
  101,9,"his abode will be the abyss<sup>4</sup>.","[4] HƒÅwiyah: the pit of Hellfire."
  101,10,"And how do you know what it is?",""
  101,11,"It is a Blazing Fire.",""
  102,1,"Competition for worldly gains distracts you [from Allah],",""
  102,2,"until you come to your graves.",""
  102,3,"No indeed! You will come to know.",""
  102,4,"Again no! You will come to know.",""
  102,5,"No indeed! If only you knew for certain<sup>1</sup>.","[1] The conclusion of this verse, ""...you would not have been distracted from preparing for the Hereafter by wealth and children."""
  102,6,"You will surely see the Blazing Fire,",""
  102,7,"Again, you will see it with absolute certainty.",""
  102,8,"Then on that Day you will surely be asked about your worldly pleasures<sup>2</sup>.","[2] i.e., of health and wealth and other comforts of the worldly life."
